OL,6,FThe HSE investigation into the
OL,7,Fincident found the ride's seat
OL,8,Frestraint system was designed with
OL,9,Felectrical and mechanical failings by
OL,10,Fthe manufacturer, Perrin Stevens
OL,11,FLimited, while the ride control system
OL,12,Fwas set up in a way that would not
OL,13,Fhave detected all failures.
OL,15,FIt said Mr Hackett failed to properly
OL,16,Fmaintain the ride, but that this was
OL,17,Fpartly due to Perrin Stevens's
OL,18,Foperator manual lacking information on
OL,19,Finspection and maintenance of the seat
OL,20,Frestraint system.
